The croissants are 120 × 6 inches = <<120*6=720>>720 inches long.
The baguettes are 60 × 2 feet = <<60*2=120>>120 feet long.

The probability of rolling a number greater than 3 is 2/3 - 1/36 = 4/9 because 2/3 minus 1/36 simplifies to 4/9.
4/9 represents 4/9 × 100% = 44.44% because 9 goes into 100 once with a remainder of 4.
44.44% is how much more likely it is that Jerry rolls a number greater than 3 than that he rolls two even numbers in a row.
